The paper deals with optimization of coded caching schemes in a network setting, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The optimization problem is formulated over a large number of variables, which suggests a focus on algorithms and complexity (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of file popularity distribution, which could be relevant to social networks and recommender systems (cs.SI).
